org.apache.spark.sql.columnar.compression

Interface CompressibleColumnBuilder<T extends org.apache.spark.sql.types.NativeType>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ColumnBuilder, Logging
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BooleanColumnBuilder, ByteColumnBuilder, DateColumnBuilder, DoubleColumnBuilder, FixedDecimalColumnBuilder, FloatColumnBuilder, IntColumnBuilder, LongColumnBuilder, NativeColumnBuilder, ShortColumnBuilder, StringColumnBuilder, TimestampColumnBuilder

    public interface CompressibleColumnBuilder<T extends org.apache.spark.sql.types.NativeType>
extends ColumnBuilder, Logging
    A stackable trait that builds optionally compressed byte buffer for a column. Memory layout of the final byte buffer is: 
    
    .--------------------------- Column type ID (4 bytes)
    |   .----------------------- Null count N (4 bytes)
    |   |   .------------------- Null positions (4 x N bytes, empty if null count is zero)
    |   |   |     .------------- Compression scheme ID (4 bytes)
    |   |   |     |   .--------- Compressed non-null elements
    V   V   V     V   V
   +---+---+-----+---+---------+
   |   |   | ... |   | ... ... |
   +---+---+-----+---+---------+
    \-----------/ \-----------/
       header         body
